resources.string:
	Disabled - the sensor is turned off completely in the viewing mode;
 	Default Off->Xxx - by default, the sensor is turned off for the application. Enable/Disable via 3xCTRL (K1: 3xR_SHIFT);
 		Off->Swipe - after exiting the off mode, there will be a Swipe mode enabled;
 		Off->Pointer - after exiting the disabled mode, there will be a Cursor mode enabled;
 	Default Swipe - the default keyboard sensor is in swipe mode. Switch via 2xCTRL (K1: 2xR_SHIFT)
 	Default Pointer - keyboard sensor in default pointer mode (moving focus/highlighting by icons, controls). Switch via 2xCTRL (K1: 2xR_SHIFT).
 	For more useful features for working with gestures and text, see the manual in chapter �
